text: Tallachula Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Tallachula is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean either "marked palmetto" or "marked rock". Variant names are "Conda Creek", "Tali Chulok Creek", and "Tallachuluk Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Kemper County, Mississippi
title: Tallachula Creek
